@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container">

    <div class="container-fluid py-3">
        <img class="w-100" src="~/images/homesite-banner.png" />
    </div>

    <div class="container-fluid py-3">
        <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

        <h2>Effective Date: July 09th 2023</h2>

        <p>We, Mason Consultancy Ltd, value the privacy of our users and are committed to protecting their personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard the information provided by our users when they access and interact with our website. By using our website, you consent to the practices described in this policy.</p>

        <h3>1. Information Collection</h3>

        <h4>1.1 Personal Information:</h4>
        <p>We may collect personal information, such as names, email addresses, and other identifiable information, when voluntarily provided by users through forms or interactions on our website.</p>

        <h4>1.2 Log Files:</h4>
        <p>Like many other websites, we may collect certain non-personal information automatically, such as IP addresses, browser types, operating systems, and referring pages. This information is used to analyze trends, administer the site, and gather demographic information.</p>

        <h3>2. Use of Information</h3>

        <h4>2.1 Personal Information:</h4>
        <p>We may use the personal information provided by users to respond to inquiries, fulfill requests, provide services, improve our website, and communicate with users about updates or relevant information.</p>

        <h4>2.2 Non-personal Information:</h4>
        <p>Non-personal information collected may be used to analyze trends, track user movement, gather demographic information, and improve the overall user experience.</p>

        <h3>3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>

        <h4>3.1 Cookies:</h4>
        <p>Our website may use cookies and similar technologies to enhance user experience, personalize content, and analyze user behavior. Users can manage their cookie preferences through their browser settings.</p>

        <h4>3.2 Third-Party Tracking:</h4>
        <p>We may engage third-party service providers to track and analyze non-personal information on our behalf. These providers may use cookies or similar technologies to collect information about users' interactions with our website.</p>

        <h3>4. Data Security</h3>

        <p>We take reasonable measures to protect the security and integrity of the information collected on our website. However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

        <h3>5. Disclosure of Information</h3>

        <h4>5.1 Sharing with Third Parties:</h4>
        <p>We do not sell, trade, or transfer users' personal information to outside parties without their consent. However, we may share personal information with trusted third parties who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or providing services to users, as long as they agree to keep the information confidential.</p>

        <h4>5.2 Legal Compliance:</h4>
        <p>We may also disclose personal information when required by law or to protect our rights, safety, or property.</p>

        <h3>6. Third-Party Links</h3>

        <h4>6.1 External Websites:</h4>
        <p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these websites. Users should review the privacy policies of these third-party sites before providing any personal information.</p>

        <h3>7. Children's Privacy</h3>

        <h4>7.1 Age Restrictions:</h4>
        <p>Our website is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware of any personal information collected from children without parental consent, we will take immediate steps to delete such information.</p>

        <h3>8. Changes to the Privacy Policy</h3>

        <h4>8.1 Policy Updates:</h4>
        <p>We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective upon posting the revised policy on our website. It is the users' responsibility to review this policy periodically for any updates or changes.</p>

        <h3>9. Contact Information</h3>

        <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at gary.mason@mason-consultancy.com</p>

        <p>By using our website, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described herein.</p>
    </div>
</div>